          "id": 201,
          "options": {
            "code": {
              "language": "plaintext",
              "mirrorPreview": false
            },
            "content": "## syfo-budstikka Dashboard\n\n**Pipeline flow:** Kafka topic -> Inbox (ingest) -> Decision (process) -> Delivery (send to channel)\n\n| Row | What it shows | High is... |\n|-----|---------------|------------|\n| **Domain Pipeline** | Messages flowing through the system: ingested, processed, dropped, delivered per channel | Processed/Delivered = good (throughput). Dropped = expected if dedup. Failed = investigate. |\n| **Worker Health** | Background worker runs, failures, and iteration duration | Runs = steady heartbeat (good). Failures = 0 is ideal. Duration: low is fast, spikes = slow. |\n| **Kafka Topic Health** | Consumer lag, records consumed, poll ratio | Lag increasing = falling behind (bad). Consumed rate tracks throughput. Empty poll = idle. |\n| **Logs** | Error log rate and raw error lines | Fewer is better. |\n| **Message Trace** | Search by event ID or reference to trace a single message through the system | Use for debugging individual messages. |\n\n**Units:** Rates are in events/sec. Duration in seconds. Lag in number of messages.\n",
            "mode": "markdown",
            "size": {
              "height": "grow"
            }
          },
          "title": "How to read this dashboard",
          "transparent": true,
          "type": "text"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "collapsed": false,
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 1,
        "w": 24,
